# Regression: the JIT `and`/`or` fall-through OP_POP must decref a HEAP left
# operand. `h and i` compiles to `push h; JUMP_IF_*_PEEK end; POP h; push i`.
# The emitter wrongly marked the PEEK ops as last_imm=1, so the fall-through POP
# took the `dec %ecx` peephole and skipped slot_decref on h. With h a heap value
# (string), that leaked one ref per truthy iteration once the loop OSR-compiled.
# Run well past the OSR threshold so the JIT thunk is exercised; the ASan leak
# gate (run_all_tests.sh under detect_leaks=1) catches a regression.
h is "a-heap-string"
i is 0
acc is 0
loop while i < 12000:
    r is h and i
    acc is acc + r
    i is i + 1

# also exercise `or` with a heap left operand that short-circuits (truthy -> returns h)
j is 0
loop while j < 12000:
    s is h or j
    j is j + 1

print of "jit-and-or-ok"
